Peak-memory instrumentation for fairchem's ParallelMLIPPredictUnit workers.

Purpose: benchmark_fairchem_native_nvt.py --mem-method patch reads the SAME
torch.cuda.max_memory_allocated statistic §7a uses, on every GP rank. Rank-0
runs in the driver process (read locally); ranks 1..N-1 are Ray actors and
need remote reset/read methods.

Concurrency note: under turbo (merge_mole=True), non-rank-0 actors enter an
infinite broadcast loop inside predict() and never return. A default Ray actor
runs one method at a time, so a queued get_peak_mem/reset_peak_mem would
deadlock behind that loop. This patch puts the two peak methods in a separate
threaded concurrency group ("mem") so they run concurrently with the looping
predict. (merge_mole=False actors return from predict each call, so the group
is a harmless no-op there.)

Apply from the fairchem checkout root (nvalchemi-toolkit/fairchem/):
  cd fairchem && git apply ../benchmark/distributed/fairchem_worker_peakmem.patch
Revert:
  cd fairchem && git apply -R ../benchmark/distributed/fairchem_worker_peakmem.patch

diff --git a/src/fairchem/core/units/mlip_unit/predict.py b/src/fairchem/core/units/mlip_unit/predict.py
index f85b916..1a61748 100644
--- a/src/fairchem/core/units/mlip_unit/predict.py
+++ b/src/fairchem/core/units/mlip_unit/predict.py
@@ -557,6 +557,19 @@ class MLIPWorkerLocal:
     def get_device_for_local_rank(self):
         return get_device_for_local_rank()
 
+    def reset_peak_mem(self) -> None:
+        # Reset CUDA peak-allocated stats so the reported peak reflects the
+        # post-warmup steady-state window (benchmark_fairchem_native_nvt.py).
+        device = getattr(self, "device", None)
+        torch.cuda.reset_peak_memory_stats(device)
+
+    def get_peak_mem(self) -> int:
+        # Peak CUDA bytes allocated on this rank's device since the last reset
+        # (the same max_memory_allocated statistic used in §7a). Returned as an
+        # int so it serializes cheaply over Ray.
+        device = getattr(self, "device", None)
+        return int(torch.cuda.max_memory_allocated(device))
+
     def _distributed_setup(
         self,
     ):
@@ -602,9 +615,18 @@ class MLIPWorkerLocal:
         return None
 
 
-@remote
+# Threaded "mem" concurrency group so reset_peak_mem/get_peak_mem run while the
+# non-rank-0 predict loop (turbo/merge_mole) never returns; "default" keeps the
+# normal one-at-a-time actor semantics for everything else.
+@remote(concurrency_groups={"default": 1, "mem": 1})
 class MLIPWorker(MLIPWorkerLocal):
-    pass
+    @ray.method(concurrency_group="mem")
+    def reset_peak_mem(self) -> None:
+        return super().reset_peak_mem()
+
+    @ray.method(concurrency_group="mem")
+    def get_peak_mem(self) -> int:
+        return super().get_peak_mem()
 
 
 class ParallelMLIPPredictUnit(MLIPPredictUnitProtocol):
